        "checksum": "36634c7152227601ce30d80d0c7092a5b5cfe1de7c20febc13eddf2692cb34f9_1_1_1_0__1",
        "ggY_vMVzD5r_text": "Hat Size Guide",
        "ggqwIs8eVQl_text": "<p>Find your perfect fit in two steps: measure your head or use a hat you already own, then convert the result with our size chart.</p>",
        "gg10kqog1Jo_text": "<p>How to Determine Your Size</p><p>If you already have a well‑fitting hat: check the size on its tag and use the conversion chart below to match it to a head measurement.</p>",
        "ggc5M72POIP_text": "<p><strong>Quick Measuring Options</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Option 1: Measuring Tape</li>\n<li>Measure as described above, then use the chart to select your size. Between sizes? Size up and add padding if needed.</li>\n<li>Option 2: Snapback Trick</li>\n<li>Adjust a snapback to your most comfortable fit, note its labeled size/setting, and map it to our chart. If between sizes, size up and pad.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Sizing</strong></p><ul>\n<li>S / 55 CM</li>\n<li>Our smallest standard size. Best if your head measures 53–54 cm.</li>\n<li>M / 57 CM</li>\n<li>Ideal for the average head size; our recommended “standard” fit.</li>\n<li>L / 59 CM</li>\n<li>Great for larger heads; the go‑to large size.</li>\n<li>XL / 61 CM</li>\n<li>Available in most styles and sold exclusively online; extra room when you need it.</li>\n</ul><p><strong>Fit Tips</strong></p><ul>\n<li>Fit is personal—choose how you want your hat to sit and feel.</li>\n<li>For extended wear (4+ hours), a slightly looser fit that sits lower can be more comfortable.</li>\n<li>Shape and style affect fit. Always check each product’s size and fit notes to ensure the best choice.</li>\n</ul>"
      }
